The paper discusses the quantum generalization of information-theoretic measures, which falls under the category of quantum information theory (cs.QI). The paper also mentions the application of these measures to distributional semantics, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques (cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS). The use of density operators to model the distributional meaning of words is a key aspect of the paper, which is a concept from quantum mechanics (cs.QI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.QI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS, and cs.IT (which covers information theory).
